{"title":"La Gazette de café du cycliste","url":"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/la-gazette/","favicon":"https://d6ea5r7lgkrij.cloudfront.net/media/favicon/stores/7/favicon-CDC.ico","elements":[{"title":"Cycling and Creativity: Rémi Clermont.","contents":"<div class=\"img-thumb\"> <a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/cycling-and-creativity-remi-clermont/\" title=\"Cycling and Creativity: Rémi Clermont\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR4nGP6zwAAAgcBApocMXEAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\" data-amsrc=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/wp/en-us/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2022/02/RideCreate_Remi-FeatureImage2-04-02-22.jpg\" alt=\"Cycling and Creativity: Rémi Clermont\"></a> </div><h2><a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/cycling-and-creativity-remi-clermont/\" title=\"Cycling and Creativity: Rémi Clermont\">LA VIE</a></h2><p><strong>Cycling and Creativity: Rémi Clermont.</strong> Rémi Clermont is creative director of Café du Cycliste. Here he speaks about creativity, and the vital role his own cycling plays in the process.</p>","link":"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/cycling-and-creativity-remi-clermont/","retrieved":1644228123115},{"title":"The Best Aligot in the World.","contents":"<div class=\"img-thumb\"> <a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/the-best-aligot-in-the-world/\" title=\"The Best Aligot in the World\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR4nGP6zwAAAgcBApocMXEAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\" data-amsrc=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/wp/en-us/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2022/02/BITW_aligot_FeatureImage3-02-02-22.jpg\" alt=\"The Best Aligot in the World\"></a> </div><h2><a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/the-best-aligot-in-the-world/\" title=\"The Best Aligot in the World\">LA VIE</a></h2><p><strong>The Best Aligot in the World.</strong> Aligot must be worked for a long time to obtain its very elastic texture. It is served with a sausage from pigs raised in the surrounding farmland of the Massif Central. </p>","link":"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/the-best-aligot-in-the-world/","retrieved":1643882569167},{"title":"Ride of the Month: January.","contents":"<div class=\"img-thumb\"> <a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/ride-of-the-month-january-2022/\" title=\"Ride of the Month January 2022\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR4nGP6zwAAAgcBApocMXEAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\" data-amsrc=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/wp/en-us/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2022/01/Duranus-19-25-01-22.jpg\" alt=\"Ride of the Month January 2022\"></a> </div><h2><a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/ride-of-the-month-january-2022/\" title=\"Ride of the Month January 2022\">LA MAISON</a></h2><p><strong> Ride of the Month: January.</strong> Exiting Nice from the north side, this ride provides a healthy mélange of architectural and natural landmarks, with a side of local legend.  </p>","link":"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/ride-of-the-month-january-2022/","retrieved":1643878943442},{"title":"Coins Cachés: Boulder, Colorado.","contents":"<div class=\"img-thumb\"> <a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/coins-caches-boulder/\" title=\"Coins Cachés Boulder\"><img src=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/wp/en-us/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2022/01/featureimage-CC-boulder-17-01-22.jpg\" alt=\"Coins Cachés Boulder\" style=\"display: inline-block;\"></a> </div><h2><a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/coins-caches-boulder/\" title=\"Coins Cachés Boulder\">ROULER</a></h2><p><strong>Coins Cachés: Boulder, Colorado.</strong> Nestled on the eastern aspect of the foothills of the Colorado Rockies, the city of Boulder (population ~100,000) is a unique and idyllic hub for outdoor recreation—including cycling.</p>","link":"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/coins-caches-boulder/","retrieved":1643878943446},{"title":"Nissa La Bella Through the Seasons: The Lookbook.","contents":"<div class=\"img-thumb\"> <a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/nissa-la-bella-through-the-seasons/\" title=\"Nissa La Bella Through the Seasons\"><img src=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/wp/en-us/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2022/01/Lookbook-Riding-Nice-2022-feature-image-13-01-22.jpg\" alt=\"Nissa La Bella Through the Seasons\" style=\"display: inline-block;\"></a> </div><h2><a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/nissa-la-bella-through-the-seasons/\" title=\"Nissa La Bella Through the Seasons\">LA MAISON</a></h2><p><strong> Nissa La Bella Through the Seasons: The Lookbook. </strong> A city by the sea but not only. A place in the sun but not just. Nice is a cycling paradise twelve months a year and always, always, worth a visit.</p>","link":"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/nissa-la-bella-through-the-seasons/","retrieved":1643878943446},{"title":"Cycling & Creativity: Sandra Sommer.","contents":"<div class=\"img-thumb\"> <a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/cycling-and-creativity-sandra-sommer/\" title=\"Cycling and Creativity Sandra Sommer\"><img src=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/wp/en-us/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2022/01/sandra_creativity-featureimage3-12-01-22.jpg\" alt=\"Cycling and Creativity Sandra Sommer\" style=\"display: inline-block;\"></a> </div><h2><a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/cycling-and-creativity-sandra-sommer/\" title=\"Cycling and Creativity Sandra Sommer\">LA VIE</a></h2><p><strong> Cycling &amp; Creativity: Sandra Sommer.</strong> As an artist, Sandra knows that inspiration can strike when you least expect it. Her most recent project came to her while exploring the mountains around Salzburg as that is when her mind is most free.</p>","link":"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/cycling-and-creativity-sandra-sommer/","retrieved":1643878943446},{"title":"Audax Lookbook: Light and Long.","contents":"<div class=\"img-thumb\"> <a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/audax-lookbook-light-long/\" title=\"Audax-Lookbook AW\"><img src=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/wp/en-us/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2022/01/Lookbook-Audax-2022-feature-image-08-01-2022.jpg\" alt=\"Audax-Lookbook AW\" style=\"display: inline-block;\"></a> </div><h2><a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/audax-lookbook-light-long/\" title=\"Audax-Lookbook AW\">COLLECTIONS</a></h2><p><strong>Audax Lookbook: Light and Long.</strong> The devil is always in the detail, especially when the ride is long.There are no half measures on full days, no short cuts to big distances.</p>","link":"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/audax-lookbook-light-long/","retrieved":1641871502794},{"title":"Autumn Colours of Seoul.","contents":"<div class=\"img-thumb\"> <a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/autumn-colours-of-seoul/\" title=\"Autumn colours of Seoul\"><img src=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/wp/en-us/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2022/01/Seoul_ImageFeature1-08-01-22.jpg\" alt=\"Autumn colours of Seoul\" style=\"display: inline-block;\"></a> </div><h2><a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/autumn-colours-of-seoul/\" title=\"Autumn colours of Seoul\">ROULER</a></h2><p><strong>Autumn Colours of Seoul. </strong>Seoul is quite a unique city. It also contains no less than five UNESCO World Heritage sites and, with the popularity of road cycling in Asia on the rise, numerous pro-cycling events take place here. But on the menu today is a scenic ride that takes us along the city’s beautiful Han River.</p>","link":"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/autumn-colours-of-seoul/","retrieved":1641871502816},{"title":"Winter on the slopes of Mont-Ventoux","contents":"<div class=\"img-thumb\"> <a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/winter-on-the-slopes-of-mont-ventoux/\" title=\"Winter on the slopes of Mont-Ventoux\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR4nGP6zwAAAgcBApocMXEAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\" data-amsrc=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/wp/en-us/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2022/01/Ventoux_Winter_FeatureImage2-04-01-22.jpg\" alt=\"Winter on the slopes of Mont-Ventoux\"></a> </div><h2><a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/winter-on-the-slopes-of-mont-ventoux/\" title=\"Winter on the slopes of Mont-Ventoux\">ROULER</a></h2><p><strong> Winter on the slopes of Mont-Ventoux</strong> On a bike, ascending the Ventoux from the Malaucène side is a classic route, but the experience is a little more unique on skis. </p>","link":"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/winter-on-the-slopes-of-mont-ventoux/","retrieved":1641871502816},{"title":"Ride of the Month: December.","contents":"<div class=\"img-thumb\"> <a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/rotm-december/\" title=\"ROTM December\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR4nGP6zwAAAgcBApocMXEAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\" data-amsrc=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/wp/en-us/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2021/12/ROTM_Luceram_FeatureImage3-22-12-21.jpg\" alt=\"ROTM December\"></a> </div><h2><a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/rotm-december/\" title=\"ROTM December\">LA MAISON</a></h2><p><strong>Ride of the Month: December. </strong> In Provence, Christmas lasts 40 days. Starting on the day of Sainte-Barbe, on the 4th of December, and lasting until Candlemas day on February the 3rd. In the small village of Luceram, nativity scenes have become a sacred tradition for its inhabitants. </p>","link":"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/rotm-december/","retrieved":1641871502817},{"title":"Caravan: Alba de Silvestro","contents":"<div class=\"img-thumb\"> <a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/caravan-alba-de-silvestro/\" title=\"Caravan Alba de Silvestro\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR4nGP6zwAAAgcBApocMXEAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\" data-amsrc=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/wp/en-us/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2021/12/alba-de-silvestro-athlete-page-22-12-21.jpg\" alt=\"Caravan Alba de Silvestro\"></a> </div><h2><a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/caravan-alba-de-silvestro/\" title=\"Caravan Alba de Silvestro\">LA MAISON</a></h2><p><strong> Caravan: Alba de Silvestro</strong> For me there’s only one difference between cycling and skimo, it’s just the season. One is for winter and the other is for summer. </p>","link":"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/caravan-alba-de-silvestro/","retrieved":1641871502818},{"title":"Exploring the Morvan.","contents":"<div class=\"img-thumb\"> <a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/sophie-gateau-exploring-the-morvan/\" title=\"Sophie Gateau: Exploring the Morvan\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR4nGP6zwAAAgcBApocMXEAAAAASUVORK5CYII=\" data-amsrc=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/wp/en-us/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2020/12/CDC_MORVAN_GATEAU_slider4-21-12-21.jpg\" alt=\"Sophie Gateau: Exploring the Morvan\"></a> </div><h2><a href=\"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/sophie-gateau-exploring-the-morvan/\" title=\"Sophie Gateau: Exploring the Morvan\">ROULER</a></h2><p><strong>Exploring the Morvan.</strong> The Morvan isn’t easily explained. A mountainous massif lying in the centre of the undulating Burgandy region. Travelling here is like taking a step back in time, and for those who love cycling, it’s a rich treasure trove waiting to be discovered. </p>","link":"https://www.cafeducycliste.com/en_us/la-gazette/sophie-gateau-exploring-the-morvan/","retrieved":1644249787186}]}